$ Python: sqlite3 - Cursor

{ description #py-sqlite3-cursor-description

  The `description` property of a → development/languages/Python/PEP/0249#py-sqlite-cursor-obj[`Cursor`] object allows to query the number of columns and their names from the most recently executed statement:
  gh|about-python|/standard-library/sqlite3/Cursor/description.py||

  This example prints:
code {
 c1     c2     c3
 ------ ------ ------
 foo    1      one
 bar    2      two
 baz    3      three
code }

}

sa:
  The → development/languages/Python/PEP/0249#pep-249-description[`description`] property of the → development/languages/Python/PEP/0249[PEP 249] `Cursor` object.
